\section*{Volume of a Cone using Spherical Coordinates}

\subsection*{Setup}
Consider a cone with base radius $a$ and height $h$. In spherical coordinates $(\rho, \theta, \phi)$:
\begin{align*}
x &= \rho \sin \phi \cos \theta \\
y &= \rho \sin \phi \sin \theta \\
